My experience from start to finish was amazing. The wait time was short and the receptionist was pleasant. Once seated our server, waitress from GOD was Jenita. She was very pleasant and friendly. She smiled every single time you saw her whether it was at our table or just helping other tables. We were about 6 deep and  undecided about certain items. Jenita brought us a few samples which made us purchase what we were once undecided about. She would come to the table dancing and singing, so much so that we joined in a couple times. As a matter of fact several of the other customers would come to our table because it was live. We were finishing up our weekend long celebration of a 30th birthday. I called the manager over to compliment her and he was just as pleasant and friendly. Dewayne,the manager, even photo bombed a picture or 2 which just added to our enjoyment. I told Dewayne, Jenita was like a York Peppermint Patty from the Swiss Alps. Lol. We had such a ball thanks to them that we stayed(and spent more money lol) way longer than the hour we planned to in the beginning. Service was so amazing, we vowed to come back very soon, when they both were there. Keep up the great work Jenita amd Dewayne.

I've been a Washingtonian transplant for the last 7 years and have always been delighted to take visiting guests to Ben's Next Door as I believe it to be a staple Capitol restaurant. My recent trip however really and truly has me rethinking taking visitors here. My server was AMAZING so this review in no part reflects on the service received. The new condensed menu is extremely lackluster. I heard that they've shifted management and it clearly shows in the removal of some staple menu items. For example, the absence of the organic cheese grits, sweet potato fries, Asian bliss wings, etc. was shocking. The inability to order from Ben's chili bowl has apparently also been severed.  I hope that this trial run of shortening the menu and testing out new things doesn't last much longer so that I can visit again and have some of the favorites that make BND memorable!
